Georges Brassens Park may not be as famous or flashy as some of Paris' other popular parks, but it's a great place for a picnic with the kids. There are plenty of spaces for kids to enjoy, including two playgrounds. Frogs live in artificial ponds, and insects abound in lush trees. It is recommended for tourists staying in the 15th arrondissement.
